  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LAC Adaptation and Risk Reduction support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a continuation of LACA42 to support and promote the integration of Adaptation and Risk Reduction across programmes and projects in the LAC region based on the LAC ARR STrategie. The main components are capacity development, Knowledge management and Learning on Adaptation and Risk Reduction. The direct beneficiaries are the key staff playing a role on ARR integration (including humanitarian, livelihoods and governance staff). The main activity of the project will be a 4 day workshop on ARR learning that will be conducted by the end of the calendar year 2010. The project will be managed by the Regional ARR Advisor.</narrative>
  </description>
